Please follow opencore's guide: https://dortania.github.io/OpenCore-Install-Guide/

Hardware:
 * Motherboard: ASUS TUF GAMING B450M PRO-S
 * CPU: AMD RYZEN 3900X
 * GPU: RX6600XT
 * SSD: Kioxia RC20
 * Sound: Motherboard Build-in lineout

Software (All):
 * OpenCorePkg: 0.8.6
 * macOS: Monterey 12.6.1
 * Platform: MacPro7,1
 * ACPI: SSDT-EC-USBX-DESKTOP.aml
 * Drivers/OpenRuntime.efi: core driver, must require
 * Drivers/HfsPlus.efi: HFS filesystem driver, must require
 * Drivers/OpenHfsPlus.efi: HFS filesystem driver, required by loading install dmg (maybe not necessary after system installed)
 * Kexts/Lilu.kext: core driver, must require
 * Kexts/VirtualSMC.kext: core driver, must require
 * Kexts/WhateverGreen.kext: GPU driver, use agdpmod=pikera here
 * Kexts/AppleALC.kext: audio driver, use alcid=1 here
 * AMD_Vanilla/patches.plist: ZEN CPU kernel patch
 * Kexts/AppleMCEReporterDisabler.kext: RYZEN CPU booting require (if not MacPro7,1, probably don't want)
 * Kexts/{SMCAMDProcessor.kext AMDRyzenCPUPowerManagement.kext}: monitor AMD CPU
 * Kexts/LucyRTL8125Ethernet.kext: 2.5G Ethernet Card (RTL8125B) require
 * Kexts/{USBToolBox.kext UTBDefault.kext UTBMap.kext}: mapping USB ports, generated by USBToolBox

BIOS Enable:
 * SVM Mode
 * Above 4G Decoding (and make sure Re-size BAR Support disabled)

BIOS Disable:
 * Serial Port
 * Fast Boot
 * Launch CSM


Work fine:
 * S3 and wakeup from s3
 * USB (after inject)
 * Audio (motherboard build-in lineout work fine, linein not tested)
 * RTL8125B 2.5G Ethernet Card
 * RX6600XT GPU don't need more driver after macOS 12.1

Issues: Currently not found.
